#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:8
msgid "生成AIは純粋置換モダナイの費用をどこまで下げられるのか"
msgstr "How Far Can Generative AI Reduce the Cost of Pure Replacement Modernization?"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:10
msgid "生成AIを開発にどう活用するか、という話はよく聞く。"
msgstr "I often hear people talk about how to use generative AI in development."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:12
msgid ""
"ただ、その入口にはいつも少し引っかかりがある。 「生成AIがすごい」という言葉は多いのに、 "
"何が一次情報で、何が期待で、何が実務上の制約なのかが見えにくい。"
msgstr ""
"Still, I always feel a slight snag at the entrance to that conversation. "
"There is plenty of talk about how “generative AI is amazing,” but it is hard "
"to tell what is primary information, what is expectation, and what is an "
"actual practical constraint."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:16
msgid ""
"今回のセッションでは、最初は生成AIを活用した開発方法論を整理しようとしていた。 Eval 駆動、Spec-first、Context "
"Engineering など、 有力そうな言葉はいくつも出てくる。"
msgstr ""
"In this session, I originally set out to organize development methodologies "
"that make use of generative AI. Terms that sound promising keep appearing: "
"Eval-driven development, Spec-first, Context Engineering, and so on."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:20
msgid "しかし、話しているうちに関心は少しずつ別の問いへ移っていった。"
msgstr "But as the conversation continued, my interest gradually shifted to a different question."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:22
msgid "生成AIは、レガシーシステムのモダナイに対して、 これまで費用対効果が合わなかった「純粋置換」を現実的にするのだろうか。"
msgstr "Can generative AI make “pure replacement” modernization realistic for legacy systems, even when it had previously been hard to justify on cost-effectiveness grounds?"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:26
msgid "ここでいう純粋置換"
msgstr "What I Mean by Pure Replacement"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:28
msgid "モダナイという言葉は広い。"
msgstr "The word modernization covers a broad range of work."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:30
msgid ""
"実際の現場では、言語の置き換えだけでなく、 システム統廃合、運用ルール変更、業務プロセス見直し、UI 改善などを含むことが多い。 "
"その場合、投資価値は説明しやすくなる。 古いものを新しくするだけでなく、業務価値も変えるからである。"
msgstr ""
"In real projects, it often includes not only replacing a programming "
"language, but also consolidating systems, changing operational rules, "
"revisiting business processes, and improving the UI. In that case, the "
"investment value is easier to explain, because the project is not merely "
"making something old new again; it is also changing the business value."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:35
msgid "一方で、今回考えたのはもっと狭い前提だった。"
msgstr "This time, though, I was thinking under much narrower assumptions."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:37
msgid "システムのスコープは変えない"
msgstr "Do not change the system scope"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:38
msgid "外部環境も変えない"
msgstr "Do not change the external environment either"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:39
msgid "画面、ロジック、タイミングを可能な限り同じにする"
msgstr "Keep screens, logic, and timing as close as possible to the original"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:40
msgid "潜在バグや暗黙ルールも含めて移植する"
msgstr "Migrate even latent bugs and implicit rules"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:41
msgid "COBOL などで動いていたものを、別言語へ置き換える"
msgstr "Replace something that ran in COBOL or a similar language with another language"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:43
msgid "つまり、業務改善を主目的にしない。 「同じものを、別の技術基盤で動かす」ことに徹する。"
msgstr "In other words, business improvement is not the main objective. The goal is to stay focused on “running the same thing on a different technical foundation.”"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:46
msgid "この前提を置くと、よくあるモダナイの説明は少し弱くなる。"
msgstr "Once I set those assumptions, the usual explanations of modernization start to feel a little weaker."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:48
msgid ""
"たとえば、外部連携先が変わるから難しい、運用ルールが変わるから難しい、 という話は、今回の前提ではいったん脇に置く。 "
"外部環境は変えないことにするし、運用もできるだけ同じにする。"
msgstr ""
"For example, arguments such as “it is hard because external integration "
"partners change” or “it is hard because operational rules change” are set "
"aside under this premise. The external environment is assumed not to change, "
"and operations are kept as close as possible to the current ones."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:52
msgid "すると問いは、かなり素朴になる。"
msgstr "Then the question becomes quite simple."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:54
msgid "これまで「お金をかける価値が見いだしにくい」とされてきた純粋置換は、 生成AIによって安くできるのではないか。"
msgstr "Could generative AI make pure replacement cheaper, even though it has long been considered hard to justify spending money on?"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:58
msgid "生成AIが効きそうなところ"
msgstr "Where Generative AI Seems Likely to Help"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:60
msgid "この問いに対して、まず期待できる部分はある。"
msgstr "There are certainly parts of this question where expectations seem reasonable."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:62
msgid ""
"生成AIは、コード変換そのものにはかなり効きそうである。 古いコードを読み、別言語の実装案を出し、 周辺のテスト雛形やドキュメントを作る。 "
"差分が出たときに、原因候補を整理することもできる。"
msgstr ""
"Generative AI seems likely to be quite useful for code conversion itself. It "
"can read old code, propose an implementation in another language, and create "
"surrounding test scaffolds and documentation. When differences appear, it can "
"also organize candidate causes."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:67
msgid "人間が一つずつ読み替えていた作業を、 AI が下書きし、人間が確認する形に変えられるなら、 変換工程の費用は大きく下がる可能性がある。"
msgstr "If work that humans used to translate piece by piece can be changed into a workflow where AI drafts and humans review, the cost of the conversion phase may drop significantly."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:71
msgid "ここまでは、かなり前向きに見てよいと思う。"
msgstr "Up to this point, I think it is fair to be fairly optimistic."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:73
msgid ""
"ただし、そこで「では純粋置換は簡単になった」とは言えない。 セッションで繰り返し出てきたのは、 "
"作ることと、同じであると説明することは別だという点だった。"
msgstr ""
"But that does not mean we can say pure replacement has become easy. What came "
"up repeatedly in the session was that building something and explaining that "
"it is the same are two different things."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:78
msgid "最後に残るのは同値性検証"
msgstr "What Remains at the End Is Equivalence Verification"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:80
msgid "純粋置換で難しいのは、正しい新システムを作ることではない。 旧システムと同じように正しく、同じように間違うことを確認することである。"
msgstr "The hard part of pure replacement is not building a correct new system. It is confirming that it is correct in the same way as the old system, and wrong in the same way as well."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:83
msgid ""
"たとえば、桁あふれ、丸め、文字コード、初期値、ソート順、NULL の扱い、 日付境界、バッチの実行順、例外時の戻り値などは、 "
"言語や実行基盤を変えると微妙にずれることがある。"
msgstr ""
"For example, overflow, rounding, character encodings, initial values, sort "
"order, NULL handling, date boundaries, batch execution order, and return "
"values on exceptions can all shift subtly when the language or runtime "
"foundation changes."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:87
msgid ""
"通常の新規開発なら、そのずれを「新しい仕様」として整理できるかもしれない。 しかし純粋置換では、ずれ自体が問題になる。 "
"古い挙動が業務上の前提になっているなら、 たとえそれが美しくない挙動でも互換対象になる。"
msgstr ""
"In ordinary new development, such differences might be organized as “new "
"specifications.” In pure replacement, however, the differences themselves "
"become the problem. If old behavior has become a business assumption, then "
"even behavior that is not elegant becomes part of the compatibility target."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:92
msgid "ここで効いてくるのが、同値性検証である。"
msgstr "This is where equivalence verification matters."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:94
msgid ""
"旧システムと新システムに同じ入力を与え、 出力、ログ、副作用、状態遷移を比較する。 過去データやゴールデンデータを使い、 "
"差分が出たら原因を調べる。 必要なら差分を許容するのか、旧挙動に寄せるのかを決める。"
msgstr ""
"Give the same input to the old and new systems, then compare outputs, logs, "
"side effects, and state transitions. Use historical data or golden data, and "
"when differences appear, investigate their causes. If necessary, decide "
"whether to allow the difference or move the new behavior closer to the old "
"one."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:100
msgid "生成AIは、この差分分析を助けられる。 テストケースを増やしたり、差分の分類をしたり、 怪しい変換箇所を指摘したりできる。"
msgstr "Generative AI can help with this difference analysis. It can add test cases, classify differences, and point out suspicious conversion points."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:104
msgid "それでも、最終的に「この範囲で同じとみなす」と決めるのは人間側である。 ここは AI が代わりに責任を取れる場所ではない。"
msgstr "Even so, humans ultimately decide, “within this range, we consider them the same.” This is not a place where AI can take responsibility on our behalf."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:108
msgid "「再現できない」より「再現できたと言い切れない」"
msgstr "Less “Cannot Reproduce” Than “Cannot Say We Reproduced It”"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:110
msgid "今回の対話で、自分の理解が少し変わったのはここだった。"
msgstr "This is where my understanding shifted a little through the conversation."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:112
msgid ""
"最初は、モダナイを阻むものとして、 タイミング依存、人間依存、外部依存、暗黙ルールのような例が挙がった。 "
"しかし、純粋置換という前提を強く置くなら、 それらは「移植対象に含めればよい」と考えることもできる。"
msgstr ""
"At first, examples such as timing dependencies, human dependencies, external "
"dependencies, and implicit rules came up as things that block modernization. "
"But if we strongly assume pure replacement, we can also think of them as "
"things that should simply be included in the migration target."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:117
msgid ""
"直列実行が必要なら、その仕組みも移す。 潜在バグがあるなら、それも前提に含める。 画面外の運用があるなら、外部環境は変えない。 "
"連携先も変わらないものとして考える。"
msgstr ""
"If serial execution is required, migrate that mechanism too. If there are "
"latent bugs, include them in the premise. If there are off-screen operations, "
"assume the external environment does not change. Treat integration partners "
"as unchanged as well."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:122
msgid "そうすると、「再現できないから無理」という説明は弱くなる。"
msgstr "Once we do that, the explanation “it is impossible because we cannot reproduce it” becomes weaker."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:124
msgid "むしろ問題は、 再現できたことをどこまで証明できるのか、 その証明にどれだけ費用がかかるのか、 そして誰がその説明責任を引き受けるのか、である。"
msgstr "The real issue is how far we can prove that we have reproduced it, how much that proof costs, and who accepts accountability for the explanation."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:129
msgid "生成AIが登場したことで、 純粋置換の変換費用は下がるかもしれない。 だが、検証責任まで自動的に消えるわけではない。"
msgstr "With the arrival of generative AI, the conversion cost of pure replacement may decrease. But responsibility for verification does not disappear automatically."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:133
msgid "この整理のほうが、いまの自分にはしっくりくる。"
msgstr "This framing feels more convincing to me right now."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:136
msgid "開発方法論として見ると何が残るか"
msgstr "What Remains When Viewed as a Development Methodology"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:138
msgid "この話は、生成AI活用の一般的な方法論にもつながる。"
msgstr "This also connects to broader methodologies for using generative AI."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:140
msgid ""
"Eval 駆動や Spec-first が重要と言われるのは、 AI による生成が強力になったからこそ、 "
"何を合格とみなすかを先に決める必要があるからである。"
msgstr ""
"Eval-driven development and Spec-first are said to be important because AI "
"generation has become powerful enough that we need to decide in advance what "
"counts as passing."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:144
msgid "純粋置換モダナイでいえば、Spec-first は新仕様を書くことだけではない。 むしろ、互換性の判定条件を書くことになる。"
msgstr "In pure replacement modernization, Spec-first is not only about writing new specifications. Rather, it means writing the criteria for judging compatibility."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:147
msgid "どの入出力を比較するのか"
msgstr "Which inputs and outputs to compare"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:148
msgid "どの副作用を比較するのか"
msgstr "Which side effects to compare"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:149
msgid "どの差分を許容しないのか"
msgstr "Which differences are not acceptable"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:150
msgid "どの差分は仕様更新として扱うのか"
msgstr "Which differences should be treated as specification updates"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:151
msgid "どの時点で受け入れ可能と判断するのか"
msgstr "At what point the replacement can be judged acceptable"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:153
msgid "この条件がないまま AI に変換させると、 コードは早く出てくる。 しかし、成功したかどうかを判断できない。"
msgstr "If we let AI perform the conversion without these criteria, code appears quickly. But we cannot judge whether it succeeded."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:157
msgid "速度を上げるほど、判定基準の弱さが後で効いてくる。 ここに生成AI活用の怖さがある。"
msgstr "The more speed increases, the more weakness in the judgment criteria matters later. This is one of the risks in using generative AI."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:161
msgid "現時点での整理"
msgstr "My Current Understanding"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:163
msgid "今回のセッションを通して、現時点では次のように考えている。"
msgstr "Through this session, my current view is as follows."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:165
msgid "生成AIは、純粋置換モダナイの可能性を広げる。 特に、コード変換、テスト雛形、差分分析、ドキュメント化の費用は下げられる。"
msgstr "Generative AI expands the possibilities for pure replacement modernization. In particular, it can reduce the cost of code conversion, test scaffolding, difference analysis, and documentation."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:168
msgid ""
"一方で、生成AIは「同じであることの説明責任」を消してくれない。 純粋置換で最後に重く残るのは、 変換作業そのものではなく、 "
"同値性検証、受入ゲート、責任分界である。"
msgstr ""
"On the other hand, generative AI does not remove the accountability for "
"explaining that two systems are the same. What remains heavy at the end of "
"pure replacement is not the conversion work itself, but equivalence "
"verification, acceptance gates, and responsibility boundaries."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:173
msgid "だから、生成AIは銀の弾というより、強力な圧縮機に近い。 作業を圧縮し、検証の材料を増やし、 人間が判断する場所を見えやすくする。"
msgstr "That is why generative AI feels less like a silver bullet and more like a powerful compressor. It compresses work, increases the material available for verification, and makes the places where humans must judge more visible."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:177
msgid "ただし、何を同じとみなすかを決めないままでは、 その力はかえって危うい。"
msgstr "But if we have not decided what counts as the same, that power can become dangerous instead."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:180
msgid "次に考えるなら、純粋置換専用のチェックリストを作りたい。"
msgstr "If I continue this line of thought, I would like to create a checklist specifically for pure replacement."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:182
msgid "互換性の判定項目"
msgstr "Compatibility judgment items"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:183
msgid "ゴールデンデータの作り方"
msgstr "How to create golden data"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:184
msgid "差分の分類ルール"
msgstr "Rules for classifying differences"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:185
msgid "受入ゲート"
msgstr "Acceptance gates"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:186
msgid "経営向けの費用対効果説明"
msgstr "A cost-effectiveness explanation for management"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:188
msgid "生成AI時代のモダナイは、 「AI が変換できるか」だけでは判断できない。"
msgstr "Modernization in the age of generative AI cannot be judged only by asking whether AI can perform the conversion."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:191
msgid "本当に問うべきなのは、 AI を使って、どこまで検証可能性を高められるかである。"
msgstr "The real question is how far we can use AI to improve verifiability."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:195
msgid "記事情報"
msgstr "Article Information"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst
msgid "著者"
msgstr "Author"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:196
msgid "mtakagishi"
msgstr "mtakagishi"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst
msgid "公開日"
msgstr "Publication Date"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2026-06-21-generative-ai-modernization-verification.rst:197
msgid "2026-06-21"
msgstr "2026-06-21"
